# =============================================================
# Cabeceras de seguridad — Cloudflare Pages / Netlify
# =============================================================
# Defensa básica contra:
#   · clickjacking          (X-Frame-Options + frame-ancestors)
#   · MIME sniffing         (X-Content-Type-Options)
#   · fuga de Referer       (Referrer-Policy)
#   · uso de APIs sensibles (Permissions-Policy)
#   · downgrade HTTPS       (Strict-Transport-Security)
#
# La CSP permite EXPLÍCITAMENTE solo lo que la web usa hoy:
#   · scripts: self + 'unsafe-inline' (Astro inlines small islands)
#   · estilos: self + Google Fonts + 'unsafe-inline' (CSS scoped de Astro)
#   · imágenes: self + data:
#   · iframes: solo Google Maps
#   · conexiones: self
#
# Si en el futuro se añade Cloudflare Turnstile, Plausible, etc., hay que
# ampliar las directivas correspondientes.

/*
  X-Frame-Options: DENY
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin
  Permissions-Policy: geolocation=(), microphone=(), camera=(), payment=(), usb=(), interest-cohort=()
  Strict-Transport-Security: max-age=63072000; includeSubDomains; preload
  Cross-Origin-Opener-Policy: same-origin
  X-DNS-Prefetch-Control: off
  Content-Security-Policy: default-src 'self'; script-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline'; style-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline' https://fonts.googleapis.com; font-src 'self' https://fonts.gstatic.com data:; img-src 'self' data: https://*.googleusercontent.com https://maps.gstatic.com https://maps.googleapis.com; frame-src https://www.google.com https://maps.google.com; connect-src 'self'; form-action 'self'; frame-ancestors 'none'; base-uri 'self'; object-src 'none'; upgrade-insecure-requests

# Cache largo para assets versionados
/_astro/*
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=31536000, immutable

/images/*
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=2592000

/fonts/*
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=31536000, immutable
